org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cole Hocker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the second night\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 424}, {\"ngram\": \"a row\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 433}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stade de France\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 456}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"the home\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 607}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 633}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"that victory bell\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 690}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hudson-Smith, the favourite in the form of his life, ran just about as well as those confident and in-the-know had billed, a time of 43.44 seconds taking another hefty chunk out of his own European record, and carrying him into the world's top five of all-time.\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1157506599745213e-28, \"text\": \"European record\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hudson-Smith\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 705}, {\"ngram\": \"the form\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 732}, {\"ngram\": \"his life\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 744}, {\"ngram\": \"the-know\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 803}, {\"ngram\": \"43.44 seconds\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 839}, {\"ngram\": \"another hefty chunk\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 866}, {\"ngram\": \"all-time\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hall, though, was four-hundredths quicker, with Muzala Samukonga of Zambia in third.\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1023, \"end\": 1029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9992310070201473, \"rank\": 0.000752410854302583, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hall\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"Muzala Samukonga\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having won bronze and then silver at successive World Championships, the fastest man on the planet in 2024 had made clear that only gold here would do.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1192, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1058}, {\"ngram\": \"successive World Championships\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"the fastest man\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1125}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1139}, {\"ngram\": \"only gold\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1177}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An expletive hurled into the Parisian night at the line, and the tears shed in hugs with family in the crowd, suggested that view is unchanged.\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1336, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An expletive\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1205}, {\"ngram\": \"the Parisian night\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1248}, {\"ngram\": \"the tears\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1263}, {\"ngram\": \"hugs\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1276}, {\"ngram\": \"family\", \"from\": 1282, \"to\": 1288}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1301}, {\"ngram\": \"view\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1322}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That it meant and mattered so much, though, is a triumph of sorts in itself.\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a triumph\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1394}, {\"ngram\": \"sorts\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1403}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three years ago, Hudson-Smith was ready to give all this up, not just his Olympic dream but life itself.\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1519, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hudson-Smith\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"not just his Olympic dream\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Covid lockdown in America, the injuries, the medical bills, they had all become too much, and he attempted suicide in his desperation for a way out.\", \"from\": 1520, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"the injuries\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1559}, {\"ngram\": \"the medical bills\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"suicide\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1634}, {\"ngram\": \"his desperation\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1663}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are incredible comebacks at every turn at these Games, but it takes nothing away from those to note this among the most extreme.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1803, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"incredible comebacks\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"every turn\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1713}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 1717, \"to\": 1728}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1750}, {\"ngram\": \"the most extreme\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1802}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But then the Birchfield Harrier's career has never stalked any predictable trajectory, never lived in the common phases of promise, potential, peak and decline.\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1818, \"end\": 1828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Birchfield_v._North_Dakota\", \"score\": 0.999999999701231, \"rank\": 2.94538012972071e-10, \"text\": \"Birchfield\", \"types\": [\"Q2334719\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Birchfield_v._North_Dakota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Birchfield_v._North_Dakota\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any predictable trajectory\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1890}, {\"ngram\": \"the common phases\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 1924}, {\"ngram\": \"promise\", \"from\": 1928, \"to\": 1935}, {\"ngram\": \"peak\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"decline\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1964}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the supposed breakthrough of a first major title, European gold in 2018, he did not dip below 45 seconds again for almost four years.\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the supposed breakthrough\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 1998}, {\"ngram\": \"a first major title\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2021}, {\"ngram\": \"European gold\", \"from\": 2023, \"to\": 2036}, {\"ngram\": \"45 seconds\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2077}, {\"ngram\": \"almost four years\", \"from\": 2088, \"to\": 2105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After running 44.75sec as a teenager in 2014, how much faster had a decade of graft, a third-of-a-life of toil, made him before tonight?\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2243, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"44.75sec\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2129}, {\"ngram\": \"a teenager\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2143}, {\"ngram\": \"a decade\", \"from\": 2173, \"to\": 2181}, {\"ngram\": \"graft\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2190}, {\"ngram\": \"a-life\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2209}, {\"ngram\": \"toil\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2217}, {\"ngram\": \"tonight\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2242}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One single second - and half of that only coming since May.\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2303, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"half\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2272}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2302}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is the level of dedication it takes just to toe the start line.\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2372, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the level\", \"from\": 2312, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"dedication\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2335}, {\"ngram\": \"the start line\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a tale of rapid, sudden progress, and a tale of anything but.\", \"from\": 2373, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a tale\", \"from\": 2379, \"to\": 2385}, {\"ngram\": \"rapid, sudden progress\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2411}, {\"ngram\": \"a tale\", \"from\": 2417, \"to\": 2423}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2435}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was bidding to become the first British man in a century, since Eric Liddell at the Paris Games of 1924, to win this title.\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2568, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2477, \"end\": 2484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.7097794310246722, \"rank\": 0.3859812042468618, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2509, \"end\": 2521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.5469837976993345e-42, \"text\": \"Eric Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a century\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2501}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 2525, \"to\": 2540}, {\"ngram\": \"this title\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So long ago was that victory, and so primitive was athletics' state, that some still considered the 400m to be a middle-distance event.\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2704, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that victory\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2597}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics' state\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2636}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400m\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2673}, {\"ngram\": \"a middle-distance event\", \"from\": 2680, \"to\": 2703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Liddell's winning time of 47.6seconds, a world record at that point, probably will not make the hurdles podium on Friday night.\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2705, \"end\": 2712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2626963978400417e-19, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a world record\", \"from\": 2744, \"to\": 2758}, {\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 2762, \"to\": 2772}, {\"ngram\": \"the hurdles\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2808}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday night\", \"from\": 2819, \"to\": 2831}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his quest to bring the story full circle with one perfect lap, Hudson-Smith came with a plan.\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2930, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his quest\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2846}, {\"ngram\": \"the story\", \"from\": 2856, \"to\": 2865}, {\"ngram\": \"full circle\", \"from\": 2866, \"to\": 2877}, {\"ngram\": \"one perfect lap\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 2898}, {\"ngram\": \"Hudson-Smith\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 2912}, {\"ngram\": \"a plan\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 2929}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He shut down almost comically early in Tuesday's semi-final, learning from defeat in Budapest last summer.\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 3037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3016, \"end\": 3024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungaroring\", \"score\": 0.9948149963222664, \"rank\": 0.0052120280622797305, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungaroring\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungaroring\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"defeat\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3012}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, he had set a new European record in qualifying for the final, but run five-hundredths-of-a-second slower in the big one itself.\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3061, \"end\": 3076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1157506599745213e-28, \"text\": \"European record\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a-second\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3141}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hardly a glaring misjudgment, hey, except the same tiny shift in the other direction would have been good enough for gold.\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3294, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hardly a glaring misjudgment\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3200}, {\"ngram\": \"the same tiny shift\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3233}, {\"ngram\": \"the other direction\", \"from\": 3237, \"to\": 3256}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Far from over-racing, though, he blamed a lack of it, a disrupted season meaning his body wasn't used to giving its full output under the stresses of fatigue.\", \"from\": 3296, \"to\": 3454, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"over-racing\", \"from\": 3305, \"to\": 3316}, {\"ngram\": \"a lack\", \"from\": 3336, \"to\": 3342}, {\"ngram\": \"his body\", \"from\": 3377, \"to\": 3385}, {\"ngram\": \"its full output\", \"from\": 3408, \"to\": 3423}, {\"ngram\": \"the stresses\", \"from\": 3430, \"to\": 3442}, {\"ngram\": \"fatigue\", \"from\": 3446, \"to\": 3453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since, he and coach Gary Evans have made preparing for the same scenario a pillar of their regime.\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3553, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3475, \"end\": 3485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Evans_(golfer)\", \"score\": 0.9404359203211077, \"rank\": 0.03333333333334321, \"text\": \"Gary Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Evans_(golfer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gary_Evans_(golfer)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same scenario\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3527}, {\"ngram\": \"a pillar\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3536}, {\"ngram\": \"their regime\", \"from\": 3540, \"to\": 3552}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are 6am gym workouts now, before his sessions hit the track.\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3568, \"end\": 3571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\", \"score\": 0.9898252290155086, \"rank\": 0.010261584896779355, \"text\": \"gym\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his sessions\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3605}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 3610, \"to\": 3619}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is hard and often he runs tired.\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3656, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But why train fresh, when you know the race of your life will also be your third of the week?\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3750, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 3692, \"to\": 3700}, {\"ngram\": \"your life\", \"from\": 3704, \"to\": 3713}, {\"ngram\": \"your third\", \"from\": 3727, \"to\": 3737}, {\"ngram\": \"the week\", \"from\": 3741, \"to\": 3749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So here it was.\", \"from\": 3752, \"to\": 3767, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just as in the World final 12 months ago, Hudson-Smith led off the bend and halfway from there to the line.\", \"from\": 3768, \"to\": 3875, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hudson-Smith\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3822}, {\"ngram\": \"the bend\", \"from\": 3831, \"to\": 3839}